  "texts": [
    "Then the left-hand side of (5.11) is equal to r d, where r is the side length of the squares.",
    "If r > 0 is small enough, then the term r d+1 ( √ d + 1) is negligible compared to r d. Therefore, if we are able to find a particular pair of squares Q and Q ′ where we also have the estimatei L d-2 i ∥π i -πi ∥ ℓ ∞ (∂Q) ≲ rε,then we obtain a contradiction.",
    "Indeed, we would then have that the right hand side of (5.11) is estimated by ≈ r d+1 + r d rε ≲ εr d. On the other hand, the left hand side itself is equal to r d, which is indeed a contradiction.",
    "This means that if such a pair of \"good squares\" exists, then for this particular choice of ρ, there is no solution to the PDE.",
    "This is exactly what also happens in the arguments of Burago and Kleiner [11] and Dymond et al [22]."
  ],
